<subSubSection id="3A7E57A8F4287545765706C14F8B5792" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="6DAA1B8CB4CA9C8FC37D255E4F9AED7E" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CAC8C7D4D2ED41AD5C27F80788989014" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Host plant and early stages are unknown. The type-series was collected in the middle of August at an altitude of ca. 900 m; a further specimen dates from early August.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="122DBB9DD3D3ECF5F6D32694261B9A63" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C8A96AB20653CCD762C069EA322B2721" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E88633312233B72FB04FF90B0C8B14E" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
<taxonomicName id="11133B5525E00A8A60B765E0EEBB63C1" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megacraspedus pentheres" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentheres">Megacraspedus pentheres</taxonomicName>
was described from seven males collected by Walsingham at Annot, Alpes-de-Haute-Provence, France (Walsingham 1920). The label dates of the examined paratype disagree with the dates published in the original decription, as 
<normalizedToken id="0003AB45B5E0B82F8BC8D6D07EB3E7CB" originalValue="’9–12.VIII.1913’">'9-12.VIII.1913'</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
